Johannesburg - Emotional team members of the Trek4Mandela expedition spoke on Wednesday at OR Tambo Airport of the heartache they experienced at the death of teammate Gugu Zulu who died during a climb on Mount Kilimanjaro. Team leader Sibusiso Vilane broke down and sobbed before members of the media, saying how sorry he was that he could not deliver on his promise to keep the loved ones of the families of the expedition membersÂ safe. As tears rolled down his face, Vilane apologised to Zulu's wife, family and the nation for not being able to bring the much loved rally champion home.  